The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Lanka want a Lords at home
Colombo: Sri Lankas cricket authorities are planning to modernize Sinhalese Sports Club (SSC) ground, the headquarters of cricket in the island, as a venue equal to Lords, the Board of Control for Cricket in Sri Lanka (BCCSL) said. BCCSL chief Thilanga Sumathipala met club authorities and discussed a plan to develop SSC as a super grade venue equal to Lords, BCCSL said in a statement. The development plan will include floodlights, a digital scoreboard, modern dressing rooms, covered stands for spectators and a museum, the statement said. The ground has hosted 22 Test matches since 1984  the most among the seven Sri Lankan Test venues. Also, 47 one-day Internationals have been played in the venue. (AP)  Copyright 
